‚ÄúExcelsior!‚Äù üí•
‚Ä¢
Happy Birthday to Stan Lee! The man who gifted the world with so much comic book splendour would have turned 97 today. Favourite cameo of his? We‚Äôve been graced with the work of this man over decades and decades of creative endeavours; artwork, comic books, and of course movies! Before his untimely passing last year, Stan Lee made many cameos in the movies based on his world of superheroes ‚Äì the one shown here is from 'The Amazing Spider-Man 2' where Stan sits and watches the graduation speeches and then remarks ‚ÄúI know that guy!‚Äù as Andrew Garfield‚Äôs Spider-Man jumps on stage to graduate.
‚Ä¢
This location is the East River Park Amphitheatre where Gwen (Emma Stone) makes an inspiring speech at the beginning of the film. It‚Äôs an exterior structure with a circular performance type of vibe ‚Äì a really cool looking location! I wasn‚Äôt sure if it was still standing or what it was used for but as I arrived I saw that it looked exactly as it did in the film‚Ä¶ just a little deserted. Stan sits and watches on these steps while the scene unfolds.
‚Ä¢
‚Ä¢

‚ÄúDogs must be carried.‚Äù
‚Ä¢
Paddington wishes you a very merry Boxing Day and hopes that everyone has had plenty of marmalade sandwiches this Christmas üêªüçØü•™ I went to travel on the same escalator that Paddington explored during his first visit to London! This is such an adorable film and a perfect little cosy adventure for Christmas time. Paddington Bear just looks so cuddly and brings so much warmth & joy along with him wherever he goes. Here he is taking his first steps in St John‚Äôs Wood tube station üöÇ
‚Ä¢
This scene is from the first Paddington film (the second is on tonight at 7.20!) and is a really funny scene where Paddington Bear travels on the London Underground for the first time ‚Äì he makes sure to follow the ‚ÄòDogs must be carried‚Äô rule! The interiors were shot at St John‚Äôs Wood tube station. It took some patience and a bit of going round and round in circles to get the shot!

‚ÄúWe‚Äôll do that together too.‚Äù
‚Ä¢
Thank you! Before all of the festivities begin this holiday season I just wanted to say THANK YOU to every single one of you for your support, your interest, and your passion for all of my travels on this page and for talking all things film with me! The internet can be such a wonderful place to connect with the world and meet so many great people! It‚Äôs been an amazing year and an even more amazing decade so I just wanted to share some of my favourite locations from earlier in the 2010s all the way up to today in 2019. What‚Äôs your favourite film of the decade?! üé¨ It‚Äôs all been such an adventure and I‚Äôve enjoyed sharing these with the world every step of the way. From the bustling streets within The Avengers to the tip-toe‚Äôing bridge in A Quiet Place ‚Äì unforgettable memories to last forever! Here‚Äôs to even more explorations in 2020. Have the most wonderful time over the Holiday season!
‚Ä¢
From Netflix, to Sony, to Fox, to everything and beyond! It‚Äôs been insane and just... wow. I never thought anything would happen with this but it‚Äôs been a blast. Whatever happens now is an added bonus. Thanks everyone!
‚Ä¢
‚Ä¢
#2019 #decade #avengers #aquietplace #marvel #pixar #characters #film #cinema #photography #travel #london #newyork #scotland #thankyou

‚ÄúNo matter what people tell you, words and ideas can change the world.‚Äù üíô
‚Ä¢
Here is Robin Williams with director Shawn Levy filming the third and final entry to the Night at the Museum trilogy. This week marks 5 years since the film premiered with it being the final time we got to see Robin Williams on-screen, he is seen here filming earlier in 2014 months before his passing. It‚Äôs always emotional to visit the British Museum for this film due to this fact. The very last time this incredible personality graced a film set and our screens as he acted his way into our hearts once again. Life is sometimes cut short so it‚Äôs always wise to appreciate what we have and what‚Äôs here in the present. Williams‚Äô laughter will live on forever and the joys of film allow that to be so!
‚Ä¢
The British Museum is a wonderful location to explore due to its beautiful architecture and, well, history! It‚Äôs nice to walk around upon the same footsteps as this amazing cast and of course Williams. Thank you for bringing this place to life everybody, from the cast to the crew, thank you! Robin Williams did have one last film released after this one but that was a voice role.
‚Ä¢
‚Ä¢
#robinwilliams #nightatthemuseum #shawnlevy #benstiller #danstevens #britishmuseum #london #history #life #film #photography #mrsdoubtfire #jumanji

‚ÄúThere has been an awakening...‚Äù
‚Ä¢
ad | Deep in the forests of Puzzlewood lies a filming location from a galaxy far far away‚Ä¶ Star Wars: The Force Awakens! There are lots of key shooting spots here at @puzzlewoodfod with this spot being where Kylo Ren and Rey have their first showdown on planet Takodana. The Rise of Skywalker is out tomorrow ‚Äì though of course you can catch the Star Wars triple bill and the midnight screenings TONIGHT at any @cineworld cinema. As always, it‚Äôs a great time to have an #CineworldUnlimited card! It‚Äôs the final chapter in this extraordinary saga so I‚Äôm sure every screen will be pretty packed! When are you seeing it?
‚Ä¢
I was guided by the lovely team at Puzzlewood who told me about what was filmed - I then went exploring solo to see what I could find! It was quite hard to distinguish the right rocks and foliage but wow it was just such an exciting location to step through and explore as previously seen in my Merlin photos.
‚Ä¢

‚ÄúThe truth is, I‚Äôm in love.‚Äù ‚ô•Ô∏è
‚Ä¢
Swipe left to see them all grown up! Love Actually (2003) vs the Love Actually Red Nose Day reunion (2017). Continuing with the festive season, here‚Äôs another scene from the beloved rom-com where Liam Neeson and Thomas Brodie-Sangster are looking over the Thames talking about love. They‚Äôre seen sitting on a bench, which is no longer there, on the London Southbank ‚Äì look at how young Thomas looks! Fast forward 14 years and here they are again ‚Äì this time a few minutes away next to the Tate Modern ‚Äì catching up on the good old days. Did you know? Sangster was only 5 years younger than Keira Knightley in the film‚Ä¶ but she was getting married and he still looked about 10‚Ä¶ let that sink in.
‚Ä¢
I love exploring this film! It‚Äôs such a pleasure being able to do so and with less than 2 weeks until Christmas it‚Äôs just too perfect üòä it‚Äôs quite emotional seeing the difference 14 years does!
‚Ä¢

‚ÄúI used to have nothing... and then I got this job, this family. But nothing lasts forever.‚Äù üíî
‚Ä¢
The trailer for Black Widow was released last week and as soon as I recognised one location I couldn‚Äôt wait to visit üé¨üï∑ This location is known as the Hankley Common in Surrey. What helped me in putting two and two together was that I came to this exact spot 2 years ago in search of a Skyfall location ‚Äì this is where the final battle ensues at Bond‚Äôs childhood home. I also read an article earlier this year, I‚Äôll link to it in my story, where the local news wrote about the filming of Black Widow here on the Common. There wasn‚Äôt much to go on at the time but I was hoping it would show up in the trailer so I could come and explore. The aesthetic and foliage was instantly reminiscent of my past experiences here. Very excited for this next entry in the MCU, thank you Marvel! üí•
‚Ä¢
The shot from the trailer has clear points of reference in the treeline and slight drop of the hill in the back ‚Äì this mirrored the landscape in one specific direction as seen in the photo. Some plants and shrubs also matched really well which was an added bonus, no surprise there as this scene was filmed only 5-6 months ago üå≥ This environment is truly stunning - it‚Äôs clear why it‚Äôs used for filming although I believe there were some concerns from the council about wildfires‚Ä¶ in the scene it does indeed look like a crash site with smoke ‚Äòn‚Äô all‚Ä¶
‚Ä¢

‚ÄúPart of the journey is the end.‚Äù
‚Ä¢
A little diversion from the usual film-related post. I wanted to share a little bit of childhood nostalgia what with the year and decade now coming to a close. We moved out of my childhood home a couple of weeks ago. It‚Äôs the only true home I‚Äôve ever known, having now lived there for over 18 years, so it was quite emotional to say the least! Before we closed those doors for the last time, I went around the house and captured some of the memories made through our time there. We have boxes full of old photographs so I chose a few and merged the past with the present ‚Äì it‚Äôs always lovely to look back and now we can look forward ü§ó 2020 is the start to a whole new decade and that sounds pretty exciting to me! üé¨
‚Ä¢
‚Ä¢

‚ÄúIt‚Äôs a Turtle Dove. I have one and you have one. As long as we each have a Turtle Dove, we‚Äôll be friends forever.‚Äù üïä
‚Ä¢
It‚Äôs time for some Home Alone magic! The original is engrained in all of our hearts but the second film is also a really lovely Christmassy entry ‚Äì watching Kevin make his way around New York City inspired me to visit some of the Home Alone 2 locations üåÉ I always admired the connection between Kevin and this lady (the wonderful Brenda Fricker), whom was just a stranger in Central Park. With a little caring consideration, Kevin sees the love within this human being and makes their Christmas whole again. This time of year is, after all, about bringing people together! Turtle Doves are a symbol of friendship, Kevin gives this lady a Turtle Dove ‚Äì he has one and she has one - as long as they each have their Turtle Dove, they‚Äôll be friends forever üíö
‚Ä¢
This scene takes place in @centralparknyc with the bridge in the back being Gapstow Bridge. I took these photos this Summer just gone. I wish I was their right now as I‚Äôm sure the bridge would look a little frostier and the lake even frozen over! Only a couple of weeks left until Christmas üéÑ
‚Ä¢

‚ÄúThe destiny of a great kingdom rests on the shoulders of a young boy, his name... Merlin.‚Äù üîÆ
‚Ä¢
I foraged deep within the magical & ancient woodlands of @puzzlewoodfod! These stunning woods are found in the heart of the Forest of Dean, Gloucestershire and they‚Äôre a key filming location to some major productions such as: Star Wars, Doctor Who, Atlantis, and as you can see here‚Ä¶ MERLIN! Did you watch Merlin when it aired? I grew up watching the show on TV ‚Äì every week I‚Äôd go over to my nans and we‚Äôd watch it together, we both loved the magical bits & bobs along with the medieval take on the Arthurian legend. This memory made visiting this location so very special, I held up each photo and was reminded of all those visits and biscuits with my nan! üé¨üíö
‚Ä¢
What an amazing place to explore! It took a while to figure out where each place was but with the help from the wonderful team at Puzzlewood, it was really great to see exactly where each different scene took place. Trees and rock formations have slightly changed over the years but for the most part, the general landscape and details have stayed recognisable.
‚Ä¢
‚Ä¢
#merlin #puzzlewood #colinmorgan #kingarthur #magic #mystical #wonder #forestofdean #scenery #bbc #mymicrogap #visitengland #photography

‚ÄúThe best way to spread Christmas cheer is singing loud for all to hear!‚Äù
‚Ä¢
It‚Äôs December 1st which means it‚Äôs officially Christmas in my books and that means magic, movies, lights, and most importantly‚Ä¶ elves! What‚Äôs your favourite Christmas film? I jingled away in the footsteps of Buddy the Elf and followed his travels through the 7 levels of the candy-cane forest, past the sea of twirly-swirly gumdrops, and then made my way through the Lincoln tunnel üç≠ I ended up in New York City where Santa came to visit and we all spread Christmas cheer by SINGING LOUD FOR ALL TO HEAR ü§ó A film with an incredible amount of hilarity and iconic moments ‚Äì one for the ages and now it‚Äôs the time of year to watch it again and again üçø
‚Ä¢
Visiting New York City through the eyes of Buddy the Elf was so magical! I had so much fun exploring where Buddy stepped with this being just one little area where this wonderful film was shot. This scene is where Buddy runs around in the revolving door without any other care in the world. Being right next to the Empire State Building, 10 W 33rd Street, this was quite easy to find.
‚Ä¢
‚Ä¢

‚ÄúIt is not a choice. It is a duty.‚Äù ‚Ä¢
ad | I teamed-up with @netflixuk to explore the royal elegance & beauty of @thecrownnetflix üëë Following in the footsteps of such golden splendour was quite an extravagant feeling ‚Äì standing where Olivia Colman, Her Majesty, spoke her speeches as she firmly commanded a country. This series is woven through the history of Britain, filmed all over the authentic landscape and architecture of the United Kingdom, and done so with the utmost respect, honour, and justice to the crown. Every member of the cast embodies their true-to-life persona with talent and suave, it‚Äôs truly a delight to watch this series grow into the arms of the nation. Season 4 is already gearing up to be an intense insight into the next chapter of the Royal family.
‚Ä¢
London. Reading. Buckingham. Windsor. Wales - just some of the stunning locations used from around the UK for filming. This production is primarily set in London with the first two shots seen here taking place at the Royal Naval College in Greenwich (also home to many Hollywood blockbusters) with the others being shot all around the lush countryside of stately homes and glorious estates. I feel extra British while writing all of this, proud to be! It was a real joy to explore all of these locations and to step through this royally stunning historical slice of television.
‚Ä¢
‚Ä¢
#thecrown #netflix #oliviacolman #clairefoy #charlesdance #mattsmith #helenabonhamcarter #queen #monarchy #royalfamily #uk #british #england #london #buckingham #locations #tv #photography #art

‚ÄúSome people live more in 20 years than others do in 80. It‚Äôs not the time that matters, it‚Äôs the person.‚Äù ‚è∞
‚Ä¢
This weekend marks the 56th anniversary of Doctor Who! Yesterday was #doctorwhoday and so I wanted to see what special surprises were in store for us‚Ä¶ they had something ready in the form of a trailer for the new series starting in January! Any immediate thoughts ü§∑üèª‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏è? Jodie Whittaker is such a fantastic actress; it‚Äôll be exciting to see where she takes the story (as well as the writers of course). David Tennant will ALWAYS be my Doctor as I grew up with him and the wonderful charismatic energy that he brought to the role. Do you have a favourite companion or scene? Any goodbye involving the Tenth Doctor and Rose always hits me where it hurts! Such an expansive show that clearly connects with so many people with it now lasting for over 56 years. Woah.
‚Ä¢
I just wanted to share a collection of Doctor Who images I‚Äôve had the pleasure of visiting over the past few months ‚Äì from Central Park to Cardiff! A few I‚Äôve never shared before but some that I just have really fond memories of capturing and love to see all of them together in a timey-whimey celebration of the Doctor and his flying blue box of possible impossibilities. Thanks for the adventures @bbcdoctorwho!
‚Ä¢
‚Ä¢

‚ÄúWould you like it... gift-wrapped?‚Äù üéÅüéÑ
‚Ä¢
Love Actually turns 16 years old today! ‚ù§Ô∏è This beloved gem of a film is everywhere this time of year and I love it all. I think every household will watch this at least once between now and the end of the year. I went to visit the location of my favourite scene in Selfridges: where Rowan Atkinson gift wraps a present for the late great Alan Rickman. The lengthy process of this scene along with the hilarious performances makes this such a funny moment in the film and I just love everything about it! Do you have a favourite scene? I can‚Äôt wait to visit some more over the festive season üé•‚ùÑÔ∏è
‚Ä¢
So much has changed in Selfridges in 15 years. You can clearly see this from the photos above. I asked around and was pointed in the direction of a gentleman in a blue suit who has been at Selfridges for 22 years! He knew exactly where the scene was shot as he had a cameo in it. The ‚ÄòWonder Room‚Äô. This room is the first room on the left if you walk in the main shop entrance via Oxford Street. The columns are the only recognisable section now; you can even see the same markings in the marble up-close.
‚Ä¢
‚Ä¢

‚ÄúWish I could be part of that woooorld!‚Äù üåç üê†
‚Ä¢
30 years ago, on the 17 November 1989, The Little Mermaid became part of our world. Its oceanic essence of Disney magic has stayed with many of us over these past decades as Ariel continues to spread the musical anthems from under the sea. I wanted to try something a little different for this film. I ventured to the coastal regions of Cornwall (Looe to be exact) to find the perfect rock to encapsulate this iconic moment in reality. A wetsuit and more patience than usual was certainly needed but even then, I knew the result would be a little uncertain. Waves crashed and the irrational fear of sharks in Cornwall kept me busy. I tried to hold it together, stretching my arms to the sky, in an attempt to keep the card away from salty splashes while also preventing my equipment from being lost in the depths. It ended up being a really fun shot to capture! With some Google Maps, internet searching, and talking with tourist groups such as Visit Cornwall - I narrowed the perfect beach down to Hannafore in Looe. It was a little uncertain but it ended up being a good choice!
‚Ä¢
Regarded as the animated classic that bought in the Disney Renaissance, this film changed the landscape of Disney Animation with it becoming a much needed box-office hit and then by being followed by a slew of other fantastic fare; Beauty and the Best, Aladdin, The Lion King, Tarzan etc. It remains relevant today and I‚Äôm sure Disney will ensure the power and importance of this film are true to the present when the remake is released in the near future.
‚Ä¢
‚Ä¢
#thelittlemermaid #30thanniversary #disney #ariel  #ocean #musical #jodibenson #animation #art #film #photography #composition #water #nature #mymicrogap #visitengland

‚ÄúWe won...‚Äù
‚Ä¢
Steve Rogers riding off into the setting sun in @centralparknyc after saving the world from Loki and his alien goons. This scene takes place at the end of ‚ÄòThe Avengers‚Äô where the heroes conduct their final farewells. In Avengers: Endgame it became pretty clear that Evans was done with the role, however in a recent interview he told Scarlet Johansson ‚Äúit‚Äôs not a hard no‚Ä¶ but it‚Äôs not an eager yes either.‚Äù Would you want to see old man Cap come back? ü§∑üèª‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏è A cameo is SURE to happen at some point. Endgame was a perfect little bookend for his character but who knows. Anything is possible. Personally though‚Ä¶ I would have preferred he sacrificed himself over Tony. Just saying.
‚Ä¢
I couldn‚Äôt wait to visit this location in Central Park! It‚Äôs such an iconic little scene at the end of the film, it‚Äôs so lovely seeing all of these supers in regular clothing just going about their business and then heading out on their way! This tree/section of road is right next to the Bethesda Terrace, the staple Central Park feature in the heart of it all - also featured in John Wick, Home Alone 2, and of course where the MAGICAL musical number takes place in Enchanted.
‚Ä¢
‚Ä¢

‚ÄúYou‚Äôre made up of everything you do...‚Äù ‚ù§Ô∏èüéÑ
‚Ä¢
ad | Christmas is in the air in London which is full of the festive filming locations of #LastChristmas! I was lucky enough to attend the premiere last night and the festive spirit was high. I might just see it again with my #CineworldUnlimited card once it‚Äôs out at @cineworld this Friday! It‚Äôs such a heart-warming film, and while it‚Äôs a little clich√©, it has what we all need right now; warmth and a celebration of life! I really enjoy @paulfeig‚Äôs work and this is certainly one I also appreciated. I loved recognising pretty much ALL of London and any other person even slightly familiar with these cobbled streets will have the same satisfying feeling. A true love letter to this beautiful city with the added bonus of George Michael!
‚Ä¢
When I first heard about this project I said to myself ‚ÄòGet ready to visit this entire film, Tom!‚Äù and as soon as that first trailer dropped in August I knew it would be possible.  I'll make sure to include each exact location in my stories! Such a lovely tale which is interwoven with the heart & soul of the city through Covent Garden‚Äôs market, St Mary‚Äôs Church, Regent Street, Phoenix Gardens and so on all the while making them shine with festivities aplenty. So much love!
‚Ä¢

Lest we forget ü•Ä
‚Ä¢
Today is Remembrance Sunday. Today we honour all those who gave their life for their country; from the two world wars and future conflicts. Every man, woman, soldier, medic, engineer, captain. Everyone who gave their tomorrow so that we could have our today. Tomorrow also marks 100 years since the first two-minute silence was observed on Armistice Day, 11th November 1919.
‚Ä¢
Dunkirk is one historical event where many lives were lost but also saved. It‚Äôs a moment in history that will never be forgotten.No photography can do justice but the least we can do is keep it in our memory and commemorate those who fought for us. I shared a collection of my Dunkirk photos last year on Remembrance Day, I often look at these and am still in awe of it all.
‚Ä¢
‚Ä¢
#lestweforget #war #peace #remembranceday #remembrancesunday #dunkirk #ww #history #honour #memories #courage #poppies #film #photography

‚ÄúI‚Äôm a ROCKET MAN!‚Äù üöÄ‚≠êÔ∏è
‚Ä¢
What a year this has been for @taron.egerton! In celebration of his 30th Birthday tomorrow I decided to take a stroll down Oakmeade lane located in Pinner. Consider this post an appreciation of everything Taron, Rocketman, and Elton John! Such an inspirational film full of colour and hope. It was stunning to see Egerton embody this musical icon, his performance was simply wonderful and his singing chops even more so. The passion he put into the role oozes through the raw emotion he gives when talking about the project ‚Äì it‚Äôs so lovely that he & Elton have become close friends through all of it. ‚ÄúHe gave me the first ever diamond earring he bought in 1972. I just knew that this was the most important role I‚Äôve played so far.‚Äù Egerton said. Hollywood giving the awe-inspiring life of Elton John what he rightfully deserves in all of its wonderful, colourful, and enigmatic glory.
‚Ä¢
Welcome to Pinner! The town in Greater London where @eltonjohn was born & raised. Little did he know that 71 years after his birth that a film about his life would be shot in the same town where he grew up ‚Äì the circle of life. This road is where the exterior of Elton‚Äôs house resides in the film as well as the joyful opening number to the film. It was fantastic to visit this location and sing along to all of the classic tunes as I went along.
‚Ä¢
‚Ä¢
#rocketman #eltonjohn #taronegerton #musical #inspiration #life #love #lgbt #acting #music #london #film #photography #filmlocation

‚ÄúSuch fun!‚Äù üé¨
‚Ä¢
This Saturday marks the 10th anniversary of the TV sitcom‚Ä¶ Miranda! It aired on the BBC on the 9th November 2009 and has since become a beloved collection of characters and jokes with Miranda Hart making us all gallop with joy wherever we go. My family absolutely loves it all too, my mum looks like Miranda and can be just as hilariously awkward which makes it all that more special. Is it popular in your household? I‚Äôm laughing to myself just thinking about moments from the series; pretending to be a mannequin in a shop window gets me every time ü§¶üèª‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏è
‚Ä¢
The majority of this show was filmed on a set at the BBC Television Centre and London Studios. However, there are also some scenes out in the real world. These were all shot around Kingston and Richmond Park, luckily this area was very recognisable as it‚Äôs the city centre. Marylebone was very familiar too as I‚Äôve often travelled out of that station. Nice and easy location scouting!
‚Ä¢
‚Ä¢
#miranda #mirandahart #10yearsofsuchfun #mirandamoments #anniversary #suchfun #bbc #comedy #funny #london #visitlondon #kingston #tomellis #uk #british #memories #family #tv

‚ÄúIt‚Äôs a leap of faith. That‚Äôs all it is. A leap of faith.‚Äù
‚Ä¢
Here‚Äôs Miles Morales leaping off of the Empire State Building. I was inspired by the immense artistic flare seen in ‚ÄòSpider-Man: Into the Spider-Verse‚Äô and wanted to translate that sense of escapist comic book landscape of 3D visuals and put it into our world. On Friday it was announced that ‚ÄòInto the Spider-Verse‚Äô was getting a sequel which I already CANNOT WAIT to see what they do with. I think we can all safely say that whatever unique Spidey style direction Phil Lord and Co decide to go down, it will surely be a feast for the eyes‚Ä¶ maybe we‚Äôll get to see Tom Holland in animated form? Maybe even Tobey Maguire and Andrew Garfield too! The first came out just under a year ago now and was the most-deserved win for Best Animated Feature at the Oscars ‚Äì simply incredible work.
‚Ä¢
